    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Offering a driver-focused 2014 BMW M3 (F80) powered by the S55 3.0L Twin-Turbocharged Inline-6. This powerplant features a closed-deck block design and a forged crankshaft, optimized for high-RPM stability and thermal efficiency. The vehicle is equipped with a 6-speed manual transmission, providing a direct mechanical link to the Active M Differential, which utilizes a multi-plate limited-slip clutch to manage torque vectoring across the rear axle. The suspension geometry remains precise, benefiting from the factory-installed CFRP strut tower brace and aluminum control arms to minimize unsprung mass. This example has been maintained with a focus on mechanical longevity; the twin-scroll turbos spool cleanly with no evidence of oil blow-by, and the cooling system remains pressurized and efficient. While the exterior shows the light patina of a well-loved performance machine, the drivetrain integrity is excellent, offering the visceral feedback and chassis rigidity expected of the M-division's engineering.",
